story of modern drama that would acknowledge the innovative contributions of the avant-garde. The anthology, which presents examples of French and Russian Symbolism, Italian Futurism, German Expression-ism, and Dada-Surrealism, as well as work by such seminal figures as Jarry, Strindberg, Artaud, and Kandinsky, illuminates the astonishing daring of these writers from many Western countries and diverse theatrical movements.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aDramay20th century. 0aExperimental dramaxHistory and criticism. 7aDRAMA / Anthologies (multiple authors).2bisacsh1 aCardullo, Bert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCardullo, Bert, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKnopf, Robert, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831105379940 cprintz978030008525940uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030013304240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300133042423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300133042/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY